HB 1209 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Firment
Abstract: Provides legislative findings and intent, a sunset date for surface water
withdrawal cooperative endeavor agreements, for the secretary's consideration of
potential introduction of invasive vegetation or wildlife species when entering
agreements, and for reporting of revenue deposited to and spent from the Aquatic
Plant Control Dedicated Fund Account to appropriate committees.
Present law provides for cooperative endeavor agreements to withdraw running surface
water with requirement for the approval by the secretary and prohibition for the resale of
withdrawn water, reserving the rights provided under present law and stating the intent of
the legislature for severability of provisions.
